{
  "texts": [
    "However, it can be challenging since adopting DP can lead to worse utility for the released data.",
    "This motivates increased research on auditing of privacy leakage via privacy attacks, which we discuss in Section 4.",
    "It also encourages DP practitioners to highlight cases where DP unlocks previously inaccessible data, as these demonstrate the opportunity for privacy technologies to enable new applications, not just provide new privacy-utility trade-offs for existing ones.",
    "Mapping the threat model: In order to establish a reliable privacy infrastructure, it is imperative to consider trust assumptions carefully, which holds for DP systems as well.",
    "Before deploying DP systems, it is essential to address several questions, such as: should we place trust in a central server (Boenisch et al., 2021; Fowl et al., 2021; L. Zhu et al., 2019), how strong an adversary can potentially be, or what kind of data requires protection?"
  ]
}